1 development within this state.
2 SECTION 2. Section 7, chapter 633, Oregon Laws 2025, is amended to read:
3 Sec. 7. (1) For the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, at the request of the Oregon Department
4 of Administrative Services, after the department consults with the Oregon Business Development
5 Department, the State Treasurer is authorized to issue lottery bonds pursuant to ORS 286A.560 to
6 286A.585 in an amount that produces $20 million in net proceeds for the purposes described in sub-
7 section (2) of this section, plus an additional amount estimated by the State Treasurer to be neces-
8 sary to pay bond-related costs.
9 (2) Net proceeds of lottery bonds issued under this section must be transferred to the depart-
10 ment for deposit in the [OBDD Economic Development Distributions Fund established under section
11 28, chapter 748, Oregon Laws 2017, for distribution to the Urban Flood Safety and Water Quality
12 District for levee system improvements along the Columbia River from Sauvie Island to the Sandy
13 River in Troutdale] Coos Bay Channel Fund established by section 15, chapter 746, Oregon
14 Laws 2007, for distribution to the Oregon International Port of Coos Bay to deepen and widen
15 the Coos Bay Federal Navigation Channel and for the design, engineering, permitting and
16 land acquisition efforts related to the Pacific Coast Intermodal Port project.
17 (3) The Legislative Assembly finds that the use of lottery bond proceeds will create jobs, further
18 economic development, finance public education or restore and protect parks, beaches, watersheds
19 and native fish and wildlife, and is authorized based on the [following findings:]
20 [(a) Levees are an integral part of the commercial and industrial infrastructure of this state; and]
21 [(b) The inspection, accreditation, certification and repair of levees will promote economic develop-
22 ment within this state.] finding that port facilities and related infrastructure are an integral
23 part of the commercial and industrial infrastructure of this state, and promote economic
24 development.
25 SECTION 3. Section 15, chapter 746, Oregon Laws 2007, as amended by section 46, chapter 599,
26 Oregon Laws 2023, is amended to read:
27 Sec. 15. (1) The Coos Bay Channel Fund is established separate and distinct from the General
28 Fund. Interest earned by the Coos Bay Channel Fund shall be credited to the fund. The moneys in
29 the Coos Bay Channel Fund are continuously appropriated to the Oregon Business Development
30 Department for the purpose described in subsection (2) of this section. The fund shall consist of
31 moneys transferred to the fund under section 13, chapter 746, Oregon Laws 2007, and [sections 44
32 and 45 of this 2023 Act] section 7, chapter 633, Oregon Laws 2025, and interest earnings on
33 moneys in the fund.
34 (2) Moneys in the fund are available to the department for distribution to the primary sponsor
35 to pay the nonfederal cost share, or the nonprivate cost share, of expenses of the project up to the
36 amounts specified in section 13, chapter 746, Oregon Laws 2007, and [sections 44 and 45 of this 2023
37 Act] section 7, chapter 633, Oregon Laws 2025, and to pay bond-related costs.
38 SECTION 4. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
39 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
40 on its passage.
